<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>CHEKOV:  I have completed the assignment, Captain. A theoretical incursion into</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, Mister Chekov. I can read, and as usual your theoretical evaluations do not tally with mine. Return to your duty and I'll let you know when your work is satisfactory.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock. Full sensor scan of the region, please.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I did give a full report</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, Mister Spock, that was the past. I'm concerned with the present. Or is it becoming too much for this crew to present me current information?</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>SOMEONE: SPOCK; No, sir. Compliance presents no problem.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KIRK:  Then, Mister Spock, comply.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Sensor scan to one half parsec. Negative, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>KIRK:  Very well.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>MCCOY [OC]:  I can find no reason for the captain's behaviour, except possibly that we've been on patrol too long without relief and diversion. He has resisted all of my attempts to run a psychological profile on him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>SULU:  Maintaining course and speed, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>KIRK:  Change course. Come about to one eight five, mark three.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>SULU:  But, sir, that'll lead us directly into the Romulan Neutral Zone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, very perceptive, Mister Sulu. I know where the course change takes us. Execute.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>SULU:  Aye, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Increasing sensor scan to one parsec. All scanners report clear. Nothing in our immediate vicinity.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>KIRK:  Better and better, Mister Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>SULU:  Captain, leaving Neutral Zone. Now entering Romulan space.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Scott enters the Bridge.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>KIRK:  Very well, Mister Sulu.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Lieutenant, when did the order come through?</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>UHURA:  Order?</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>SCOTT:  From Starfleet. The order to enter the Neutral Zone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>UHURA:  There's been no order I know of, Mister Scott.</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Surely the Captain couldn't be doing this on his own authority.</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>KIRK:  If you two have complaints, you can bring them out into the open.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A sinister shape appears on the viewscreen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>SCOTT:  That's a Klingon ship! But it couldn't be, not in this area.</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Intelligence reports Romulans now using Klingon design.</td></tr>

<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>KIRK:  Sound Red Alert. Man battle stations. Stand by main phasers.</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>UHURA:  Battle stations. All hands, battle stations.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>SPOCK:  A second ship has appeared. (another one decloaks) Correction, there are now three. We are surrounded.</td></tr>

<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant Uhura, code a message to Starfleet Command. Advise them of our situation. Include all log entries to this point.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>UHURA:  Aye, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock, your sensors read clear. What happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I have a theory, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>UHURA:  Captain Kirk, I'm receiving a class two signal from the Romulan vessel.</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>KIRK:  Put it on the main viewing screen, Lieutenant, and complete that message to Starfleet Command.</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>UHURA:  Aye, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>TAL [on viewscreen]:  (a thin male) You have been identified as the star ship Enterprise, Captain James T. Kirk last known to be in command.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>KIRK:  Your information is correct. This is Captain Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>TAL [on viewscreen]:  I am Sub-commander Tal of the Romulan fleet. Your ship is surrounded, Captain. You will surrender immediately, or we will destroy you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant. (mutes sound) They want something, or they would have destroyed us by now.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>SPOCK:  True, Captain. That would be standard Romulan procedure.</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>KIRK:  It's my ship they want, and very badly.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>SPOCK:  It would be a great prize.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant. (sound on) Save your threats. If you board this ship, I'll blow it up. You'll gain nothing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>TAL [on viewscreen]:  Who is that beside you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>KIRK:  My first officer, Commander Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>TAL [on viewscreen]:  Vulcan. (his communicator beeps and he answers it) Yes, Commander. Yes, Commander. No one should decide quickly to die, Captain. We give you one of your hours. If you do not surrender your ship at the end of that time, your destruction is certain. We will be open to communication should you wish it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>KIRK:  You understand that Starfleet Command has been advised of the situation?</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>TAL [on viewscreen]:  The subspace message will take three weeks to reach Starfleet. The decision is yours, Captain. One hour.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Briefing room</td></tr>
<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>KIRK:  The design of the ship is the same. Mister Spock, you said you had a theory on why your sensors didn't pick up the new ships until they were upon us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I believe the Romulans have developed a cloaking device which renders our tracking sensors useless.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>KIRK:  If so, Romulans could attack in Federation territory before we knew they were there, before a vessel or planet could get even begin to get their defences up.</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>SCOTT:  They caught us right enough.</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, that's a brilliant observation, Mister Scott. Do you have any other helpful opinions?</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>SCOTT:  We've not got many choices.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>KIRK:  We have three. We can fight and be destroyed, or we can destroy the Enterprise ourselves and keep her from the Romulans. Or we can surrender. Opinions, gentlemen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>SCOTT:  If the Enterprise is taken by Romulans, they'll know everything there is to know about a starship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>SPOCK:  If we had not crossed the Neutral Zone, on your order, you would not now need our opinions to support a decision which should never have had to be made.</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim, you ordered us? You had no authority!</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>KIRK:  Dismissed, Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim!</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>KIRK:  I said dismissed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: McCoy leaves.</td></tr>

