<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>KIRK:  Put them on the screen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>UHURA [OC]:  Aye, aye, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>TAL [on monitor]:  My commander wishes to speak with you, Captain Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>KIRK:  Put him on.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>TAL [on monitor]:  The commander wishes to see you and your first officer aboard this vessel. It is felt this matter requires discussion.</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>KIRK:  Why should we walk right into your hands?</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>TAL [on monitor]:  Two of my officers will beam aboard your vessel as exchange hostages while you are here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>KIRK:  What guarantee do we have they'll beam aboard our ship once we're on yours?</td></tr>

<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>TAL [on monitor]:  Granted, we do not easily trust each other, Captain, but you are the ones who violated our territory. Should it not be we who distrust your motives? However, we agree to simultaneous exchange.</td></tr>

<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>KIRK:  Give us your transporter co-ordinates. We're beaming aboard.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Transporter room</td></tr>
<tr id="L80"><td><a href="#L80">80</a></td><td>KIRK:  One final order, Engineer Scott. If we do not return, the Enterprise must not be taken. If the Romulans attempt it, you're to fight, and if necessary, destroy yourselves. Is that clear?</td></tr>

<tr id="L81"><td><a href="#L81">81</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Perfectly clear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L82"><td><a href="#L82">82</a></td><td>KIRK:  Energise.</td></tr>

<tr id="L83"><td><a href="#L83">83</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: As Kirk and Spock beam out, two Romulans beam in. Once solid, they draw their weapons. Scott scowls.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Romulan Commander's office</td></tr>
<tr id="L84"><td><a href="#L84">84</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The figure in the curved chair swivels round to reveal that the Commander is a woman in a uniform that barely covers her bottom, and thigh-length boots held up by suspender belt.</td></tr>

<tr id="L85"><td><a href="#L85">85</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Captain Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L86"><td><a href="#L86">86</a></td><td>KIRK:  Commander. I'm honoured.</td></tr>

<tr id="L87"><td><a href="#L87">87</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  I don't think so, but we have an important matter to discuss. And your superficial courtesies are an overture to that discussion. You are the first officer?</td></tr>

<tr id="L88"><td><a href="#L88">88</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L89"><td><a href="#L89">89</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  I speak first with the Captain. You may wait outside.</td></tr>

<tr id="L90"><td><a href="#L90">90</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock and the two guards leave</td></tr>

<tr id="L91"><td><a href="#L91">91</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  The matter of trespass into Romulan space is one of galactic import, a violation of treaties. Now I ask you simply, what is your mission here?</td></tr>

<tr id="L92"><td><a href="#L92">92</a></td><td>KIRK:  Instrument failure caused navigational error. We were across the Neutral Zone before we realised it, then we were surrounded by your ships before we could get back.</td></tr>

<tr id="L93"><td><a href="#L93">93</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  A starship? One of the Starfleet's finest vessels? You're saying instrument failure as radical as you suggest went unnoticed until you were well past the Neutral Zone?</td></tr>

<tr id="L94"><td><a href="#L94">94</a></td><td>KIRK:  Accidents happen. Cut off back-up systems malfunction. We were due for overhaul two months ago.</td></tr>

<tr id="L95"><td><a href="#L95">95</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  I see. But you were able to navigate with this malfunction?</td></tr>

<tr id="L96"><td><a href="#L96">96</a></td><td>KIRK:  The error was corrected.</td></tr>

<tr id="L97"><td><a href="#L97">97</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  But I doubt it'll clear you of espionage.</td></tr>

<tr id="L98"><td><a href="#L98">98</a></td><td>KIRK:  We were not spying, Commander.</td></tr>

<tr id="L99"><td><a href="#L99">99</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Your language has always been most difficult for me, Captain. Perhaps you have another word for it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L100"><td><a href="#L100">100</a></td><td>KIRK:  You're grossly mistaken if you think we were there</td></tr>

<tr id="L101"><td><a href="#L101">101</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Captain, if a Romulan vessel ventured far into Federation territory without good explanation, what would a starbase commander do? You see, it works both ways. I hardly believe you are the injured party. Spock, come in.</td></tr>

<tr id="L102"><td><a href="#L102">102</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock and the guards enter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L103"><td><a href="#L103">103</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  The captain has made his statement.</td></tr>

<tr id="L104"><td><a href="#L104">104</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L105"><td><a href="#L105">105</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  I must admit some surprise on seeing you, Spock. We were not aware of Vulcans aboard the Enterprise.</td></tr>

<tr id="L106"><td><a href="#L106">106</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Starfleet is not in the habit of informing Romulans of its ships' personnel.</td></tr>

<tr id="L107"><td><a href="#L107">107</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Quite so. Yet there are certain ships, certain officers, that are known to us. Your situation appears most interesting.</td></tr>

<tr id="L108"><td><a href="#L108">108</a></td><td>KIRK:  What earns Spock your special interest?</td></tr>

<tr id="L109"><td><a href="#L109">109</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  He is a Vulcan. Our forebears had the same roots and origins. Something you wouldn't understand, Captain. We can appreciate the Vulcans, our distant brothers. I have heard of Vulcan integrity and personal honour. There's a well-known saying, or is it a myth, that Vulcans are incapable of lying?</td></tr>

<tr id="L110"><td><a href="#L110">110</a></td><td>SPOCK:  It is no myth.</td></tr>

<tr id="L111"><td><a href="#L111">111</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Then tell me truthfully now, by your honour as a Vulcan, what was your mission?</td></tr>

<tr id="L112"><td><a href="#L112">112</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I reserve the privilege of speaking only when it will not violate my honour as a Vulcan.</td></tr>

<tr id="L113"><td><a href="#L113">113</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  It is unworthy of a Vulcan to resort to subterfuge.</td></tr>

<tr id="L114"><td><a href="#L114">114</a></td><td>SPOCK:  You're being clever, Commander. That is unworthy of a Romulan. It is not a lie to keep the truth to oneself.</td></tr>

<tr id="L115"><td><a href="#L115">115</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Then there is a truth here that remains unspoken.</td></tr>

<tr id="L116"><td><a href="#L116">116</a></td><td>KIRK:  You've been told everything. There's nothing else to say.</td></tr>

<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  There is Mister Spock's unspoken truth. You knew of the cloaking device that we have developed. You deliberately violated Romulan space with a blatant spy mission, by order of the Federation.</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>KIRK:  We've been all through that, Commander!</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  We have not even begun! There's no force that I can use on a Vulcan that will make him speak. That is a fact. But there are Romulan methods completely effective against humans and human weaknesses.</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>SPOCK:  You would not resort to them, Commander. They would prove ineffective against the captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Then they will leave him dead, or what might be worse than dead. But I will know your unspoken truths.</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>KIRK:  Let her rant. There's nothing to say.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I cannot allow the captain to be further destroyed. The strain of command has worn heavily upon him. He's not been himself for several weeks.</td></tr>

<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>KIRK:  That's a lie!</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>SPOCK:  As you can see, Captain Kirk is a highly sensitive and emotional person. I believe he has lost the capacity for rational decision.</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>KIRK:  Shut up, Spock!</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I'm betraying no secrets. The commander's suspicion that Starfleet ordered the Enterprise into the Neutral Zone is unacceptable. Our rapid capture demonstrates its foolhardiness.</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>KIRK:  You filthy liar!</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I am speaking the truth for the benefit of the Enterprise and the Federation. I say now and for the record, that Captain Kirk ordered the Enterprise across the Neutral Zone on his own initiative and his craving for glory.</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>KIRK:  (having to be held back by the guards) I'll kill you, you filthy traitor! I'll kill you! I'll kill you!</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>SPOCK:  He is not sane.</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  (into comm. system) Attention, Enterprise, I am speaking to you from the Romulan flagship.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>COMMANDER [OC]:  The USS Enterprise, under command of Captain James T. Kirk, is formally charged with espionage. The testimony of First Officer</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>COMMANDER [OC]:  Spock was highly instrumental in confirming this intrusion into Romulan space was not an accident. First Officer Spock's testimony was specific that your ship was not under orders from Starfleet Command or the Federation council to perform such a spy mission.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Romulan Commander's office</td></tr>
<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  It was Captain Kirk who was solely responsible. Since the crew had no choice but to obey orders, the crew will not be held responsible. Therefore, I am ordering Engineer Scott, presently in command of the Enterprise, to follow the Romulan flagship</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>COMMANDER [OC]:  To our home base. You will there be processed and released to Federation Command. Until judgment is passed, Captain Kirk will be held in confinement.</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Security, put our two Romulan hostages in the brig. Lieutenant Uhura, give me a channel to that ship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>UHURA:  Channel is open, Mister Scott, and you are tied in.</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>SCOTT:  This is Lieutenant Commander Scott. The Enterprise takes no orders, except those of Captain</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Romulan Commander's office</td></tr>
<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>SCOTT [OC]:  Kirk, And we will stay right here until he returns. And if you make any attempt to board or commandeer the Enterprise, it will be blown to bits along with as many of you as we can take with us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  You humans make a brave noise. There are ways to convince you of your errors.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>KIRK:  Did you hear that, you coward? You've betrayed everything of value you ever knew. Did you hear the sound of human integrity?</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  Take him to the security room.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk is dragged out, struggling.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  A Vulcan among humans. Living, working with them. I would think the situation would be intolerable to you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I am half Vulcan. My mother is a human.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  To whom is your allegiance then? Do you call yourself Terran or Vulcan?</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Vulcan.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>COMMANDER:  How long have you been a Starfleet officer, Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Eighteen years.</td></tr>

